'''Radiation trapping''', '''imprisonment of resonance radiation''', '''radiative transfer of spectral lines''', '''line transfer''' or '''radiation diffusion''' is a phenomenon in [[physics]] whereby [[radiation]] may be "trapped" in a system as it is emitted by one [[atom]] and [[Absorption (electromagnetic radiation)|absorbed]] by another.<ref>[http://raptor.physics.wisc.edu/talk/part_2d2.htm Primer on Collisions<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>* {{Citation | surname1 = Molisch | given1 = Andreas F. | surname2 = Oehry | given2 = Bernard P. | date = 1998 | title = Radiation Trapping in Atomic Vapours | publisher = Oxford University Press | place = Oxford | isbn = 0-19-853866-9 | url = https://books.google.com/?id=JoELZdSUzKEC&printsec=frontcover&dq=isbn:0198538669
| accessdate = June 18, 2006 }}.</ref>
